.TH "lpfc_scan_finished" 9 "lpfc_scan_finished" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_scan_finished \- method for SCSI layer to detect whether scan is done
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_scan_finished
.BI "(struct Scsi_Host *shost "  ","
.BI "unsigned long time "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shost" 12
pointer to SCSI host data structure.
.IP "time" 12
elapsed time of the scan in jiffies.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is called by the SCSI layer with a SCSI host to determine
whether the scan host is finished.

Return codes
0 - SCSI host scan is not over yet.
1 - SCSI host scan is over.
.SH "NOTE"
there is no scan_start function as adapter initialization will have
asynchronously kicked off the link initialization.
